BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:sVsaTnHbjgC1w9Ikrbl1_
SUMMARY:China and India: Conflict and Cooperation in the (De)Globalization 
	Era
DTSTAMP:20260409T031212Z
DTSTART:20260421T230000Z
DESCRIPTION:The 2026 Peter L. Lee Endowed Lecture in East Asian Culture and
	 Civilization will be given by T.V. Paul\, Distinguished James McGill Prof
	essor of the Political Science Department at McGill University.\n\n \n\n20
	26 Peter L. Lee Endowed Lecture in East Asian Culture and Civilization\n\n
	Speaker: T.V. Paul\n\nLocation: Casey Commons\n\n4:00 pm Reception\n\n4:30
	-6:00 pm Lecture\n\n \n\nFree and open to Students\, Faculty and Community
	 Members\n\nPlease register to RSVP if interested\n\n \n\nChina and India:
	 Conflict and Cooperation in the \\(De\\)Globalization Era\n\nThe relation
	s between Asian giants China and India have been characterized by a mixtur
	e of conflict and cooperation. Since the 1962 territorial dispute\, there 
	have been intermittent flare-ups with no clear end in sight. However\, Ind
	ia and China seem to agree on many issues such as trade\, global financial
	 reforms and climate change. This talk explores the multifaceted causes of
	 the peculiar contours of this “managed rivalry.” A broad range of topics 
	such as territory dispute\, status\, resources\, conceptions of regional a
	nd world order\, strategic culture\, balance of power and deterrence strat
	egies will be analyzed. The mitigating role of asymmetrical economic inter
	dependence adopted by the two states as well as their common membership in
	 institutions such as BRICS\, SCO and G20 have helped periodic crises from
	 escalating into wars. The China-India relationship is likely to shape 21s
	t century international politics and the Indo-Pacific regional order profo
	undly.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/china-and-india-co
	nflict-and-cooperation-in-the-de-globalization-era/18260270/2026-04-21T00\
	n\nFrom SEAtoday - Community & Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/china-and-india-conflict-
	and-cooperation-in-the-de-globalization-era/18260270/2026-04-21T00
LOCATION:Northwest Worklofts (Commons)\, 107 West Denny Way\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-community
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Community & Civic
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:6WnSk57HN8CpSJK50yfxd
SUMMARY:An Evening with Amy Cordalis
DTSTAMP:20260409T031212Z
DTSTART:20260421T230000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for an evening with Amy Bowers Cordalis\, a Yurok mothe
	r\, fisherwoman\, attorney\, and nationally recognized leader in Indigenou
	s environmental advocacy. Amy has served as General Counsel of the Yurok N
	ation and now leads the Ridges to Riffles Indigenous Conservation Group\, 
	where she works to advance sovereignty and protect cultural and natural re
	sources\, including the undamming of the Klamath River.\n\n \n\nHer leader
	ship has earned global recognition\, including the United Nations Champion
	s of the World Laureate and a place on the 2024 TIME100 Climate List honor
	ing the most influential voices in climate action. She is also the author 
	of The Water Remembers \\(Hachette\, 2025\\) and will have copies of the b
	ook available for purchase at the event.\n\n \n\nOpen to the public at no 
	cost\, this event offers an opportunity to engage with a powerful voice fo
	r land\, water\, and Indigenous futures. Early registration is encouraged\
	, as space and tickets are limited.\n\n \n\nCo-sponsored with the Institut
	e for Catholic Thought and Culture and the Center for Environmental Justic
	e and Sustainability.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/an-
	evening-with-amy-cordalis/18260269/2026-04-21T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Commun
	ity & Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/an-evening-with-amy-corda
	lis/18260269/2026-04-21T00
LOCATION:Sinegal Center for Science and Innovation\, 200\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-community
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Community & Civic
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:Q16VEs5YhE2i4IxywA84e
SUMMARY:City Council Regular Hybrid Meeting
DTSTAMP:20260409T031212Z
DTSTART:20260422T000000Z
DESCRIPTION:January 29\, 20206 - Notice is hereby given that the Mercer Isl
	and City Council will hold a public hearing at its Hybrid Meeting on Tuesd
	 ay\, March 3\, 2026\, at approximately 5pm\, to receive comments on Ordin
	a nce No. 26-02\, renewing interim regulations in MICC 19.16.010 related t
	o emergency shelters and housing\, transitional housing\, and permanent su
	pportive housing in response to E2SHB 1220.\n\nThe public hearing will b e
	 held in person and using Zoom. The public will have the opportunity to c 
	omment during the public hearing by either attending in person\, calling i
	n\, or logging onto the meeting via Zoom. Written comments may be submitte
	d to the City of Mercer Island by e-mail to council@mercerisland.gov until
	  such time that the public hearing is adjourned.\n\nDetailed instruction 
	s on how to comment live during the public hearing will be available onlin
	 e on or before February 25\, 2026\, at: https://www.mercerisland.gov/city
	council.\n\nAndrea Larson\, CMC\n\nCity Clerk\n\nNotice:\n\nCity Council C
	alendar - January 29\, 2026\n\nCity Council Agenda Distribution List - Jan
	uary 29\,  2026\n\nWebsite Public Notice - January 29\, 2026\n\nMercer Isl
	and Reporter - January 28\, 2026\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/
